9.26.18  5:26 am   What do you think of services like Spotify, both as an artist and a consumer?

     as a consumer i don't use it. i got hooked on playing things off the hard-drive at an early age, and when the streaming services came out i didn't want any part of it. spotify also had this crazy quirk where nothing i ever searched for was ever available, and only fake versions turned up instead. it is all wrong for me, as a listener. as an artist, it is also extremely cumbersome to deal with. but that doesn't matter, i must pursue the actual places where people are actually listening to music, and try to get my music to those places as much as possible

I don't want to be confused with him or make him uncomfortable by "competing" with him but i also don't know what else i would go by. Thoughts?
